## Installation and Setup вљ™пёЏ

### Step 1: Clone the Repository

```
git clone https://github.com/your-username/smart-text-editor.git
```

### Step 2: Navigate to Project Folder

```
cd task-3
```

### Step 3: Install Client Dependencies

```
cd client
npm install
```

### Step 4: Install Server Dependencies

```
cd ../server
npm install
```

### Step 5: Run Backend Server

```
npm start
```

Server will run on:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

### Step 6: Run Frontend Application

Open a new terminal:

```
cd client
npm start
```

Application will run on:

```
http://localhost:3000
```

---

## How It Works вљЎ

1. User writes text in the editor.
2. Toolbar buttons apply formatting using JavaScript commands.
3. Word count updates automatically as the user types.
4. Documents can be saved and reopened using local storage.
5. Users can export their written content as a PDF file.

